I can't reduplicate this on demand...

Occasionally when I use the up-arrow (to get previous history commands) the  
last character is doubled.

Is this a termcap problem?  Here is the vt100 I am using... with the leading  
spaces trimmed so it doesn't wrap...

d0|vt100|vt100-am|vt100am|dec vt100:\
 :do=^J:co#80:li#24:cl=\E[;H\E[2J:sf=2*\ED:\
 :le=^H:bs:am:cm=5\E[%i%d;%dH:nd=2\E[C:up=2\E[A:\
 :ce=3\E[K:cd=50\E[J:so=2\E[7m:se=2\E[m:us=2\E[4m:ue=2\E[m:\
 :md=2\E[1m:mr=2\E[7m:mb=2\E[5m:me=2\E[m:\
 :rf=/usr/lib/tabset/vt100:\
 :rs=\E>\E[?3l\E[?4l\E[?5l\E[?7h\E[?8h\E[;r\E[0m\E(B\E)B\E[2J:\
 :ks=\E[?1h\E=:ke=\E[?1l\E>:\
